%h1 NI Week 2015
%p
  In my opinion, NI Week was everything it needed to be. There were
  #{ext_link 'many presentations', 'https://decibel.ni.com/content/groups/niweek-2015?view=documents'}
  given, lots of information exchanged, business cards passed around, prizes awarded
  (I won a Raspberry PI kit auctioned off by Sixclear at the LAVA BBQ!), and
  generally a good time, so definitely worth the trip! There were a few parts of the
  keynotes that I feel fell a little short. Maybe my expectations were just too
  high? Maybe. But, for instance, as
  #{ext_link 'Brandon Steele', 'https://www.linkedin.com/pub/brandon-steele/4/375/b17'}
  pointed out, if you are showing off a cool new bike that you can monitor using
  LabVIEW, you definitely should hire a professional to ride it around the stage
  instead of just picking it up and spinning the tires.

%p
  Despite the lack of “pop”, Endigit was especially excited because two of NI’s
  company highlights during the keynote presentations were Endigit clients!

%ul
  %li
    #{ext_link 'Steve Aposhian', 'https://www.linkedin.com/pub/steve-aposhian/2/a69/884'},
    a Utah native, and
    #{ext_link 'FireFly Equipment', 'http://fireflyequipment.com/'} showed off his
    huge sod farming machine. They even brought it out onto the floor and started it
    up. Had it pick up and palletize a bunch of sod!
  %li
    #{ext_link 'Innovari', 'http://www.innovari.com/'}, one of Endigit’s key
    clients, was also highlighted on stage for the work they are doing  with the
    electric grid.
